  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>potato[es]</strong> into fries – these are your <strong>mixed fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1688737304803-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1688737304803-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1688737304803-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1688737304803-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-3-1688737304803-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>mixed</strong> <strong>fries</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the fries are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1688737308555-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1688737308555-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1688737308555-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1688737308555-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-3-1688737308555-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> in half lengthways</p><p>Slice each half into 2 pieces (roughly the size and shape of fish fingers) so that you are left with 4 <strong>basa</strong> <strong>strips </strong>per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1688737318117-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1688737318117-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1688737318117-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1688737318117-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1688737318117-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate and a splash of <strong>milk</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Coat the <strong>basa</strong> <strong>strips</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add it into the <strong>milk</strong> and finally press it into the <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1688737321509-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1688737321509-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1688737321509-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1688737321509-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1688737321509-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>breaded basa strips</strong> to a separate<strong> baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>fish goujons</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-3-1688737325439-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
